==English==

{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English [[ac|āc]], from Germanic ''*aiks''.  Cognate with Dutch [[eik]], German [[Eiche]], Swedish [[ek]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/əʊk/}}
*{{AHD|ōk}}, {{SAMPA|/<tt>@Uk</tt>/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊk|-əʊk]]
*{{audio|en-us-oak.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{countable}} A [[tree]] of the genus ''[[Quercus]]'', bearing [[acorn]]s and having [[lobed]] [[leaf|leaves]].
# {{uncountable}} The [[wood]] of the oak.
# (colour) a rich brown colour, like that of oak wood.
